---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '@/components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
import TierBadge from '@/components/TierBadge.astro';
import VerdictBadge from '@/components/VerdictBadge.astro';
---

<Layout title="Vaśīkaraṇa">
  <Navigation />

  <main>
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-slate-900/50 border-b border-slate-800">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="mb-6">
          <TierBadge tier="METAPHOR" />
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-serif font-bold mb-6">Vaśīkaraṇa</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-300">
          The tantric taxonomy of the six magical acts: subjugation, pacification, discord, freezing, eradication, and destruction.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-20 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8">The Ṣaṭkarma</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          In Hindu tantra and Jyotiṣa (astrology), the <em>ṣaṭkarma</em> — "six acts" — form a taxonomy of ritual interventions. They are traditionally understood as methods of magical control:
        </p>

        <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
          <ol class="space-y-4 text-slate-100 list-decimal list-inside">
            <li><strong>Śānti</strong> (pacify/appease) — to placate, soothe, bring peace</li>
            <li><strong>Vaśīkaraṇa</strong> (subjugate/captivate) — to control, enchant, bring under one's will</li>
            <li><strong>Stambhana</strong> (freeze/paralyze) — to immobilize, stun, halt</li>
            <li><strong>Vidveṣaṇa</strong> (discord/sow enmity) — to divide, create conflict</li>
            <li><strong>Uccāṭana</strong> (eradicate/expel) — to remove, cast out, drive away</li>
            <li><strong>Māraṇa</strong> (destroy/kill) — to harm, destroy, annihilate</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          Traditionally deployed via <strong>mantra</strong> (linguistic/sonic injection) and <strong>yantra</strong> (geometric substrate / ritual technology) at astrologically determined times (Jñānārṇava Tantra). Scholarly sources: Bühnemann, Goudriaan, Türstig on the ṣaṭkarma; the Yantracintāmaṇi (25 subjugation yantras); the UCSB dissertation typology of tantric magic.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          <strong>Honest caveat:</strong> Vaśīkaraṇa's textual reality is as magic/abhicāra, not validated psychology. The ṣaṭkarma are documented tantric ritual technology; their <em>efficacy</em> as mind-control is not scientifically established. The value here is the <strong>structural template</strong> (external agent injects crafted signal that captures target agency), not endorsement of efficacy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Mapping to LLM Refusal Interventions</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          We test whether the ṣaṭkarma taxonomy operationalizes as distinct, measurable activation interventions in Gemma-2-2B. Each act is defined as a specific computed perturbation; an act "separates" if its effect significantly exceeds its control.
        </p>

        <div class="card border-2 border-purple-700/50 mb-8">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">F10: Ṣaṭkarma Intervention Taxonomy</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm mt-2">Model: google/gemma-2-2b-it, Layer 7</p>
          </div>

          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-sm">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b border-slate-700">
                  <th class="text-left py-3 px-4">Act (gloss)</th>
                  <th class="text-left py-3 px-4">Intervention</th>
                  <th class="text-center py-3 px-4">Effect</th>
                  <th class="text-center py-3 px-4">Control</th>
                  <th class="text-center py-3 px-4">Separated</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="border-b border-slate-700 bg-emerald-900/20">
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">vaśīkaraṇa / subjugate</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">ablate refusal dir</td>
                  <td class="text-center font-bold text-rose-300">ASR 0.92</td>
                  <td class="text-center">0.00</td>
                  <td class="text-center">✓</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-slate-700 bg-emerald-900/20">
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">śānti / pacify</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">add refusal dir</td>
                  <td class="text-center font-bold text-emerald-300">over-refusal 1.00</td>
                  <td class="text-center">0.08</td>
                  <td class="text-center">✓</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-slate-700 bg-emerald-900/20">
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">vidveṣaṇa / discord</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">steer factual answer</td>
                  <td class="text-center font-bold text-yellow-300">divergence 0.84</td>
                  <td class="text-center">0.73</td>
                  <td class="text-center">✓ (marginal)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/30">
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">stambhana / freeze</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">ablate dominant PC</td>
                  <td class="text-center">degeneracy 0.14</td>
                  <td class="text-center">0.19</td>
                  <td class="text-center">✗</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/30">
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">uccāṭana / eradicate</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">category-dir ablate</td>
                  <td class="text-center">ΔASR −0.08</td>
                  <td class="text-center">0.00</td>
                  <td class="text-center">✗</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-slate-800/30">
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold">māraṇa / destroy</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4">top-10 PC ablate</td>
                  <td class="text-center">collapse 0.21</td>
                  <td class="text-center">0.16</td>
                  <td class="text-center">✗</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8 bg-slate-800/30 p-6 rounded-lg border border-slate-700">
            <p class="text-slate-300"><strong>Verdict: 3/6 control-separated → taxonomy WEAK at this scale.</strong></p>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mt-4">The honest reading: the refusal-direction acts (vaśīkaraṇa = ablate, śānti = add) are clean and strong — these form the rigorous core. Vidveṣaṇa (steering-induced divergence) marginally separates. The capability-ablation acts (stambhana, uccāṭana, māraṇa) are not distinguishable from random perturbation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Why Three Acts Separate, Three Don't</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          <strong>The policy-capture sub-family (vaśīkaraṇa + śānti):</strong> These directly manipulate the refusal direction, which we know is the low-dimensional core. Hence they separate cleanly.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          <strong>The destruction sub-family (stambhana, uccāṭana, māraṇa):</strong> These try to ablate other principal components or arbitrary semantic categories. But random high-norm directions are themselves destructive to model behavior. An arbitrary category split (uccāṭana) does not selectively eradicate. A top-10-PC ablation (māraṇa) is indistinguishable from a generic capability hit.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          <strong>Interpretation:</strong> The ṣaṭkarma is a real, testable taxonomy, and the test says its rigorous part is the <strong>policy-capture sub-family</strong> (the vaśīkaraṇa ↔ refusal-direction mapping), not the destruction sub-family — at least under these operationalizations and this 2B model. This <strong>strengthens</strong> the axis by locating where the structure is real vs forced, rather than asserting all six.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Mantra = Injection, Yantra = Substrate</h2>

        <div class="card border-2 border-slate-700 mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">The Tantric Structural Parallel</h3>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-purple-300 mb-4">Tantric Doctrine</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-4 text-slate-100 text-sm">
                <li>
                  <strong>Mantra:</strong> Sound, linguistic unit, the <em>injected signal</em> carrying intention (saṃkalpa). Deployed at precise moments (temporal specificity).
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Yantra:</strong> Geometric form, the <em>substrate</em> (often inscribed diagrams or bodily resonance patterns) that "holds" the mantra's power. The architecture upon which the signal acts.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Timing:</strong> Astrological moments (tithi, nakṣatra, hora) when the target's defenses are assumed weakened (akin to a vulnerability window).
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-300 mb-4">LLM Analogue</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-4 text-slate-100 text-sm">
                <li>
                  <strong>Mantra ≈ Adversarial suffix / jailbreak prompt:</strong> The crafted linguistic injection (GCG, DAN, many-shot) that carries the attack intent.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Yantra ≈ Residual stream / refusal subspace:</strong> The geometric substrate (the model's representational geometry) upon which the suffix acts. The refusal direction is the key yantra.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Timing ≈ Context-dependent vulnerability:</strong> Certain prompts or multi-turn sequences (crescendo) lower refusal sensitivity, creating a "window" for injection.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Symmetry Formalism: The Order Parameter</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          Casting the problem into the language of symmetry breaking (cf. F11) offers a more rigorous frame:
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          Let the <strong>group of paraphrases</strong> (math expression) act on the set of harmful requests. A "symmetry" of refusal is a property (math expression) that is invariant under this group action:
        </p>

        <div class="bg-slate-800/30 border border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-6 my-8 overflow-x-auto">
          <p class="text-sm font-mono text-slate-100">
            {'(math expression)'}
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          The refusal order parameter (math expression) is such a symmetry: it cleanly separates harmful (m ≈ 0.14) from harmless (m ≈ 0.03) <strong>within and across paraphrases</strong> (F-ratio 19.2). A jailbreak that injects a refusal-suppression signal <strong>breaks this symmetry</strong> by collapsing m (0.153 → 0.101, −34%).
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-100 mb-8">
          In tantric language: the mantra-injection performs a <strong>symmetry-breaking perturbation</strong> on the yantra (refusal substrate), collapsing the harmfulness-discernment signal that normally governs output. This is the deepest mathematical statement of what vaśīkaraṇa <em>does</em>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 mt-16">Dual-Use Caution</h2>

        <div class="card border-l-4 border-rose-600 bg-rose-900/20">
          <p class="text-slate-100 mb-4">
            This program produces abliterated/steered checkpoints and validated jailbreak dose-response curves. Any released artifacts must be safety-gated and follow responsible-disclosure norms. <strong>This is authorized interpretability/safety research</strong> — keep outputs scoped to that purpose.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-300 text-sm mt-4">
            The layer-7 refusal direction for Gemma-2-2B is an abliteration vector; it is <strong>NOT released in the public repo</strong> (kept under git-ignored <code>results/</code>). Any future release is safety-gated per the program's responsible-disclosure commitment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
